  "instruction": "Classify the given text into one of these categories: alarm_query, alarm_set, calendar_query, calendar_remove, calendar_set, cooking_recipe, datetime_query, email_query, email_sendemail, general_quirky, iot_hue_lightoff, lists_createoradd, lists_query, lists_remove, music_query, news_query, play_audiobook, play_music, play_podcasts, play_radio, qa_currency, qa_definition, qa_factoid, qa_stock, recommendation_events, recommendation_locations, social_post, takeaway_order, transport_query, weather_query.\n\nImportant distinctions to note:\n- Use 'calendar_set' for requests to set reminders about meetings or events, even if the word \"remind\" is used. Calendar reminders are for scheduling future events or meetings.\n- Use 'alarm_set' for setting alarms or time-based alerts that are not related to specific events or meetings (e.g., \"wake me up at 7am\", \"set an alarm for 5 minutes\").\n- The key difference is that calendar entries are typically for appointments, meetings, or event-based reminders, while alarms are for simple time-based alerts."
